accessibility.text: Until now we have only talked about projects that deal with outputs. Here is a project that deals with inputs, believe me, it’s cool!
The way a push button works with Galileo is that when the button is pushed, the voltage goes LOW. The Galileo reads this and reacts accordingly.
A pull up resistor will be used too, to keep the voltage HIGH when the button is not pressed.

The easiest way to hook up the pushbutton is to connect two wires to any opposite corners. Connect any pin on pushbutton 1 to ground (GND). Connect the opposite diagonal pin of the pushbutton to digital pin 2.
